00:39:04,199 --> 00:39:05,320
Mr. Fan, you should

712
00:39:06,719 --> 00:39:07,880
have you finished lately?

713
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:28,039
That's all for today.

714
00:39:28,719 --> 00:39:29,800
Ministers, you may leave.

715
00:39:33,079 --> 00:39:35,400
Yes, Your Majesty.

716
00:39:42,519 --> 00:39:43,280
Mr. Fan,

717
00:39:44,519 --> 00:39:45,440
you should stay

718
00:39:45,679 --> 00:39:47,000
and talk with me.

719
00:39:56,639 --> 00:39:57,639
You can come up.

720
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:20,320
Mother,

721
00:40:21,280 --> 00:40:22,480
I'm so happy

722
00:40:22,480 --> 00:40:23,519
to see Fan Xian

723
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:24,719
that I forgot about
diplomatic etiquette.

724
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:25,960
So happy?

725
00:40:26,239 --> 00:40:27,519
Please forgive me.

726
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:06,039
Are you the poetic genius of Nanqing?

727
00:41:07,679 --> 00:41:08,639
I'm so flattered.

728
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:10,239
to bear the title.

729
00:41:11,239 --> 00:41:12,360
Fan Xian pays respects to
Your Majesty the Empress Dowager.

730
00:41:14,719 --> 00:41:15,679
Rise.

731
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:21,480
His Majesty loves your poems.

732
00:41:24,719 --> 00:41:27,000
Your Majesty,
what do you want to talk with him?

733
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:31,480
Just talk about poems casually.

734
00:41:32,599 --> 00:41:33,920
Please allow us.

735
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:36,519
You're the emperor.

736
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:38,480
You can make the call.

737
00:41:39,440 --> 00:41:40,880
If you want to talk poems with him,

738
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:42,599
just go ahead.

739
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:48,400
The hall is too majestic.
It's not a place to talk.

740
00:41:49,440 --> 00:41:51,599
I'd like to go out for a walk
with Fan Xian.

741
00:41:52,039 --> 00:41:53,480
Mother, you must be tired after
handling all the political affairs.

742
00:41:54,039 --> 00:41:55,400
You'd better go back to
your palace for a rest.

743
00:41:57,760 --> 00:41:59,559
Is the hall too majestic,

744
00:42:00,159 --> 00:42:03,199
or am I too majestic?

745
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:05,639
Mother, it's known to the world that

746
00:42:05,960 --> 00:42:07,280
you're elegant and kind.

747
00:42:08,400 --> 00:42:09,159
Well then.

748
00:42:09,679 --> 00:42:11,199
Let me walk

749
00:42:11,199 --> 00:42:12,280
with you.

750
00:42:13,199 --> 00:42:15,920
Mother, you must be tired.
How dare I bother you?

751
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:19,239
That being said,

752
00:42:20,159 --> 00:42:22,360
I might as well go back to my palace.

753
00:42:24,360 --> 00:42:25,920
Your Auntie is here.

754
00:42:26,599 --> 00:42:27,960
If you want to talk casually,

755
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:31,559
your Auntie can keep you company.

756
00:42:38,199 --> 00:42:39,679
Mother, see you.

757
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:48,599
Auntie,
when did you get back to Shangjing?

758
00:42:49,079 --> 00:42:50,039
I got back yesterday.

759
00:42:50,719 --> 00:42:52,840
My teacher is afraid there might be too
many villains in the imperial palace,

760
00:42:53,159 --> 00:42:54,440
so he sends me here.

761
00:42:55,119 --> 00:42:55,639
Villains?

762
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:58,639
Yes, there are all kinds of villains
in the world.

763
00:42:59,199 --> 00:43:00,639
Some are cunning and deceitful,

764
00:43:00,719 --> 00:43:02,039
some are shameless and insidious,

765
00:43:02,559 --> 00:43:05,320
and some may even drug others.

766
00:43:05,639 --> 00:43:06,480
It's impossible to guard against them.

767
00:44:08,840 --> 00:44:10,199
Let's have a rest here.

768
00:44:12,199 --> 00:44:13,320
Holding on to the balustrade clean,

769
00:44:13,840 --> 00:44:15,920
I feel the chill of the wind
blowing watery smoke onto my face.

770
00:44:15,920 --> 00:44:17,039
Good!

771
00:44:18,119 --> 00:44:20,960
I sing aloud dispersing
the fleeting clouds apace.

772
00:44:23,440 --> 00:44:26,039
Excellent! Wonderful!

773
00:44:28,199 --> 00:44:29,920
There are many people
trying to flatter me.

774
00:44:31,440 --> 00:44:33,199
But Fan Xian, you're the first one

775
00:44:34,079 --> 00:44:36,280
to flatter me in a careless way.

776
00:44:37,079 --> 00:44:37,960
I'm so flattered.

777
00:44:40,679 --> 00:44:42,440
Auntie, you're seldom here.

778
00:44:42,920 --> 00:44:44,159
Now that you're here,

779
00:44:44,599 --> 00:44:46,159
you can appreciate the scenery.

780
00:44:48,880 --> 00:44:50,159
The imperial palace is so beautiful

781
00:44:51,239 --> 00:44:52,119
that I never thought of

782
00:44:52,679 --> 00:44:54,320
taking a walk outside the palace walls.

783
00:44:56,280 --> 00:44:57,039
Mr. Fan,

784
00:44:57,599 --> 00:44:59,400
how do you like the scenery here?

785
00:44:59,599 --> 00:45:00,119
Good.

786
00:45:00,800 --> 00:45:01,800
What is good?

787
00:45:04,719 --> 00:45:05,320
There are trees.

788
00:45:11,159 --> 00:45:12,199
You're so good at making compliments.

789
00:45:17,679 --> 00:45:18,920
Mr. Fan, do you know

790
00:45:19,960 --> 00:45:21,639
why I ask you to stay?

791
00:45:22,199 --> 00:45:23,280
Your Majesty, please tell me.

792
00:45:23,920 --> 00:45:24,760
There're two reasons.

793
00:45:25,599 --> 00:45:26,159
Firstly,

794
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:28,480
I love your talent in literature.

795
00:45:28,760 --> 00:45:30,400
I can hardly bear
to put down the Red Mansions

796
00:45:30,480 --> 00:45:31,599
written by you under a pseudonym.

797
00:45:33,320 --> 00:45:35,360
However, it does take a long time

798
00:45:35,760 --> 00:45:36,719
for you to release the new chapter.

799
00:45:37,119 --> 00:45:38,360
I'll try my best to finish it.

800
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:40,880
Secondly, it's your poem collection.

801
00:45:41,599 --> 00:45:43,519
You actually composed
so many marvelous poems overnight.

802
00:45:44,519 --> 00:45:45,920
Once it's released,

803
00:45:47,199 --> 00:45:48,800
even I dare not compose any poems.

804
00:45:50,440 --> 00:45:51,719
I'm so flattered,

805
00:45:52,000 --> 00:45:52,840
but your Majesty's poem is really good.

806
00:45:53,480 --> 00:45:54,119
Take a seat.

807
00:46:01,920 --> 00:46:03,559
Actually, there's another reason.

808
00:46:06,039 --> 00:46:07,599
Mr. Fan, you went all the way up north.

809
00:46:08,119 --> 00:46:09,840
How do you like the scenery in Beiqi?

810
00:46:10,119 --> 00:46:12,119
The scenery is picturesque and the land
is endowed with nature's treasures.

811
00:46:12,920 --> 00:46:14,320
How is it compared to Nanqing?

812
00:46:14,320 --> 00:46:15,000
It's far better.

813
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:15,800
The palace walls of Nanqing

814
00:46:15,800 --> 00:46:16,880
are much lower

815
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:17,719
and closer to ditches,

816
00:46:17,719 --> 00:46:18,639
which smell like horse urine.

817
00:46:25,119 --> 00:46:26,519
When Auntie said you're a rascal,

818
00:46:26,719 --> 00:46:27,599
I didn't believe her.

819
00:46:28,639 --> 00:46:30,960
Today by meeting you in person,
I think she's right about you.

820
00:46:34,320 --> 00:46:35,360
It should be the first time

821
00:46:35,519 --> 00:46:36,960
for me to meet your Auntie.

822
00:46:37,159 --> 00:46:38,320
How could she make such a comment?

823
00:46:39,400 --> 00:46:40,199
You really haven't met her before?

824
00:46:41,199 --> 00:46:42,119
No.

825
00:46:43,559 --> 00:46:45,400
She's Haitang. Do you remember?

826
00:46:48,119 --> 00:46:49,800
So she's Miss Haitang,

827
00:46:49,800 --> 00:46:50,880
the Beiqi Saintess.

828
00:46:51,360 --> 00:46:52,280
I've heard so much of you!

829
00:46:55,079 --> 00:46:56,119
In my opinion, Mr. Fan,

830
00:46:56,119 --> 00:46:57,079
you must have a poor memory.

831
00:47:00,599 --> 00:47:02,400
It really is my first time

832
00:47:02,400 --> 00:47:03,599
to meet her.

833
